{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "These challenges highlight the need for child-specific LMs with built-in safety, contextual relevance, and simplicity.",
    "(Lin et al., 2021) employs a masking strategy that targets \"entities\" identified by a domain-specific pretrained named entity recognizer (NER) model.",
    "Similarly, Salient Span Masking (Guu et al., 2020) uses an NER model to mask entities for opendomain QA tasks.",
    "Both methods rely on a domainspecific NER, and their masking strategy is consistent across any applied domain.",
    "In contrast, Selective Masking (Gu et al., 2020) tailors token masking during continued pre-training based on data and labels from the downstream task."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
